article_title: HHS analysts: Average HealthCare.gov plan premium rose 8.8 percent
article_text:
HealthCare.gov is missing age information for 53 2016 enrollees. State-based exchanges are missing that information for 1,190 enrollees.

Federal government analysts have published a big batch of public health insurance exchange plan enrollment data for the 2016 open enrollment period — and, possibly, hints of lingering data tracking problems at some of the state-based exchanges.

See also: CMS: HealthCare.gov has mailed its 1095-As
